# TwinleafStory - Cursor Rules

## Project
Custom MapleStory v83 private server + native client mono-repo.
- Client source at repo root (C++17, CMake/Ninja, macOS ARM64)
- server/ = Java server emulator (Cosmic fork, Maven)
- tools/ = WZ-to-NX converter (wztonx), NX structure inspector (nxdump)
- docs/ = Architecture, milestones, protocol reference, setup guides

## Client Conventions (C++)
- C++17, CMake, Ninja. Build: `cd build && cmake -G Ninja .. && ninja`
- OpenGL 2.1 via GLAD (NOT GLEW). GLFW3 for windowing.
- Audio: miniaudio (NOT OpenAL/Alure). ma_decoder_init_memory pipeline.
- NX files: memory-mapped via NoLifeNx (includes/nlnx/). Paths are v83-specific.
- CRITICAL: v83 NX paths differ from v167+. Always verify with nxdump before coding.
- Comment v83 deviations with `// v83:` prefix.
- Use `nl::nx::map` for map data (NOT map001/mapLatest/mapPretty).
- MapleButton(null_node) is safe (empty textures, no-op draw). Sprite/Texture(null_node) also safe.
- Packet encryption: AES-OFB, pre-v118 key, MAPLEVERSION=83.
- NX files required: see Util/NxFiles.h (15 v83 files, single Map.nx).

## Server Conventions (Java)
- Java 17, Maven. Build: `cd server && ./mvnw clean package`
- Cosmic fork (P0nk/Cosmic). AGPL-3.0 license.
- Key files: SendOpcode.java, RecvOpcode.java, PacketCreator.java, Hwid.java
- NPC scripts: JavaScript in server/scripts/

## Assets
- NX files (~6.9GB) NOT in git. Symlinked into build/ from external directory.
- WZ source (~6.7GB) NOT in git. Community repack .IMG format.
- Convert: tools/wztonx/build/wztonx -c <file.wz>
- Inspect: tools/nxdump/build/nxdump <file.nx> <path> [depth]

## Git
- Branch: feature/client-*, feature/server-*, fix/*, docs/*
- Commits: imperative mood, prefix with [client], [server], [tools], or [docs]
- Never commit: *.nx, *.wz, build/, Settings, .DS_Store

## AI Context
- Detailed context in CLAUDE.md files at root and each subdirectory.
- Root CLAUDE.md has full opcode tables, v83 NX path reference, architecture.
- server/CLAUDE.md has Cosmic architecture, protocol notes.
- tools/CLAUDE.md has tool usage and asset pipeline.
- docs/ has milestones, reference material, setup guides.
